        "id": "cmrp62uo10003jx1vb88srpij",
        "type": "markdown",
        "content": "Lost people and forgotten voices breathe and pulse in a dreamlike exploration of image and sound. This experimental short brings the submerged ancient Tamil city back to life.\nPoompuhar, the capital of the early Chola kingdom was once a thriving port for maritime trade with Rome, Greece and South East Asia. Excavations suggest parts of this lost city remain submerged today either due to a tsunami or rising sea levels. Featured in the Tamil epic Silappathikaram and Tamil Sangam literature as 'Kaveripoompattinam', Poompuhar is a vital line to Tamil culture and history.\n\nSources: Kaveripattinam excavations by KV Sounderrajan, audio excerpts of Thiru M. Karunanidhi, and the Tamil feature film Poompuhar (1964)",
